newsitem.title: USA: Nebraska cattle market quiet, no sales - private.
newsitem.headline: Nebraska cattle market quiet, no sales - private.

text.p: Nebraska feedlot cattle markets were inactive following Tuesday's active sales, market sources said.
"There were no trades because for all intents and purposes there's nothing left to sell," one source said.
About 80,000 head sold Tuesday at $112.00 per cwt on a dressed basis and $70.00 on a cash basis, both up $2.00 from last week's top prices.
This week's showlist was estimated at 70,000 to 76,000 head. Sharply higher beef prices fueled the active packer demand, they said.
